<paragraph blockId="8.[145,761,916,1183]" pageId="8" pageNumber="331">
<emphasis box="[145,262,916,937]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="331">Remarks:</emphasis>
The capitulums of this specimen (QM G337590) were not swollen, while capitulums of the examined specimens of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schultze" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[509,761,977,998]" class="Anthozoa" family="Epizoanthidae" genus="Epizoanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="8" pageNumber="331" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="fatuus">
<emphasis box="[509,761,977,998]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="331">Epizoanthus fatuus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(NSMT-Co 1757, NSMT-Co 1758) were swollen when contracted. On the other hand, numbers of tentacles and mesenteries were the same between QM G337590 and the examined specimens of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schultze" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[521,628,1100,1122]" class="Anthozoa" family="Epizoanthidae" genus="Epizoanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="8" pageNumber="331" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="fatuus">
<emphasis box="[521,628,1100,1122]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="331">E. fatuus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, we here preliminarily identify the examined specimen as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schultze" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[177,441,1161,1183]" class="Anthozoa" family="Epizoanthidae" genus="Epizoanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="8" pageNumber="331" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="fatuus">
<emphasis box="[177,320,1161,1182]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="331">Epizoanthus</emphasis>
aff. 
<emphasis box="[369,441,1161,1182]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="331">fatuus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
